        <header>Animal Group Names</header>

        <p>For many species of animals, there are names that we use to refer to a group of them - like a flock of birds. Here are a few you might not know.</p>

        <h3>Contents:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#foxes">A skulk of foxes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#cats">A clowder of cats</a></li>
            <li><a href="#rabbits">A colony of rabbits</a></li>
            <li><a href="#dogs">A pack of dogs</a></li>
            <li><a href="#penguins">A waddle of penguins</a></li>
            <li><a href="#horses">A team of horses</a></li>
            <li><a href="#cheetahs">A coalition of cheetahs</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="foxes">A skulk of foxes</h2>

        <p>Also called a "leash."</p>

        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/fox.png"class="silverframe">

        <h2 id="cats">A clowder of cats</h2>

        <p>Also called a "pounce", "glaring", "kindle", or "clutter."</p>

        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/cat.png"class="goldframe">

        <h2 id="rabbits">A colony of rabbits</h2>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/rabbit.png"class="greenframe">

        <h2 id="dogs">A pack of dogs</h2>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/retriever.png"class="redframe">
        <h2 id="penguins">A waddle of penguins</h2>
        <p>Also as known as a raft, rookery, colony and huddle.</p>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/penguins.png"class="silverframe">
        <h2 id="horses">A team of horses</h2>
        <p>Also as known as a harras, rag, stud and string.</p>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/horse.png"class="greenframe">
        <h2 id="cheetahs">A coalition of cheetahs</h2>
        <p>There seems to be only ONE group name for cheetahs which is "coalition".</p>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/animals/cheetah.png"class="goldframe">
